  "text": "The LLVM loop vectorization infrastructure is composed of the following key files:\n\n1. **LoopVectorizePass** - The main pass entry point defined in `llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.h` (line 131). This is a PassInfoMixin-based pass that drives the entire vectorization process.\n\n2. **LoopVectorizeOptions** - Configuration structure defined in `llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.h` (line 85). This provides options to control whether loops are only vectorized/interleaved when explicitly forced or by default.\n\n3. **LoopVectorizationLegality** - The legality checker class defined in `llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.h` (line 261). Its header file contains the class definition, with implementation in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.cpp`. This class determines whether a loop can legally be vectorized by checking memory access patterns and scalar operation constraints.\n\n4. **LoopVectorizationCostModel** - The cost analysis class defined in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp` (line 882). This class estimates the profitability of vectorization and determines optimal vector widths using the TargetTransformInfo analysis.\n\n5. **VPlan** (Vectorization Plan) - The hierarchical CFG representation of a vectorized loop defined in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h` (line 4491), with implementation in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp`. VPlan encodes various vectorization decisions and represents the vectorized loop body as a hierarchy of VPBasicBlocks and VPRegionBlocks."
}

